|work=[[UKChartsPlus]]|accessdate=May 12, 2016}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|41\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2006/hot-100-songs|title=Hot 100 Songs \u2013 Year-End 2006|work=Billboard|accessdate=December 2, 2019}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|8\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US Rhythmic (''Billboard'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2006/rhythmic-songs|title=Rhythmic Songs \u2013 Year-End 2006|work=Billboard|accessdate=December 2, 2019}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Germany|relyear=2006|certyear=2018|title=Ridin'|artist=Chamillionaire feat. Krayzie Bone|type=single|award=Gold|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|relyear=2006|certyear=2013|title=Ridin'|artist=Chamillionaire|type=single|award=Silver}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|relyear=2005|certyear=2007|title=Ridin'|artist=Chamillionaire|type=single|award=Platinum|number=4|salesamount=4,000,000}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==Release history==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n! Country\n! Date\n|-\n| United States\n| January 12, 2006\n|-\n| United Kingdom\n| September 14, 2006\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles of the 2000s#2006|List of ''Billboard'' Hot 100 number-one singles of the 2000s]]\n*[[List of Billboard Rhythmic number-one songs of the 2000s#2006|List of ''Billboard'' Rhythmic number-one songs of the 2000s]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{YouTube|CtwJvgPJ9xw}}\n* {{MetroLyrics song|chamillionaire|ridin}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Chamillionaire}}\n\n[[Category:2006 singles]]\n[[Category:Chamillionaire songs]]\n[[Category:Krayzie Bone songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Chamillionaire]]\n[[Category:Gangsta rap songs]]\n[[Category:Works about police brutality]]\n[[Category:Songs against racism and xenophobia]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:UK R&B Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Internet memes]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Krayzie Bone]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Play-N-Skillz]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Single by Chamillionaire featuring Krayzie Bone}}\n{{About|the Chamillionaire single|the M\u00fda song|Ridin' (M\u00fda song)}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Ridin'\n| cover      = RidinChamillionaireKB.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Chamillionaire]] featuring [[Krayzie Bone]]\n| album      = [[The Sound of Revenge]]\n| released   = January 12, 2006\n| format     = {{hlist|[[CD single]]|[[Single (music)|12\" single]]}}\n| recorded   = 2005\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Gangsta rap]], [[southern hip hop]]\n| length     = 5:02<br/>4:08 (radio edit)\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Universal Records|Universal]]|[[Chamillitary Entertainment|Chamillitary]]}}\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Chamillionaire|Hakeem Seriki]]|[[Play-N-Skillz|Juan Salinas, Oscar Salinas]]|[[Krayzie Bone|Anthony Henderson]]}}\n| producer   = [[Play-N-Skillz]]\n| chronology = [[Chamillionaire]]\n| prev_title = [[Turn It Up (Chamillionaire song)|Turn It Up]]\n| prev_year  = 2005\n| next_title = [[Get Up (Ciara song)|Get Up]]\n| next_year  = 2006\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Krayzie Bone]]\n | type       = singles\n | prev_title = [[Get'chu Twisted]]\n | prev_year  = 2005\n | title      = Ridin'\n | year       = 2006\n | next_title = [[Spit Your Game]]\n | next_year  = 2007\n}}\n}}\n[[File:Ridin Dirty.ogg|thumb|right|\"Ridin'\", from the Chamillionaires debut solo album Sound of Revenge.]]\n\n\"'''Ridin''''\" is a song by American rapper [[Chamillionaire]], released as the [[lead single]] from his debut studio album ''[[The Sound of Revenge]]'' (2005). The song, [[hip hop production|produced]] by [[Play-N-Skillz]], features a [[guest appearance]] from fellow American [[rapper]] [[Krayzie Bone]], of [[Bone Thugs n Harmony]]. Its title is often incorrectly assumed to be \"Ridin' Dirty\", due to the chorus. The lyrics concern [[racial profiling]] and [[police brutality]], as well as the [[stereotyping of African-Americans]] driving a vehicle with [[illegal narcotics|drugs]] or other [[contraband]] on the inside (\"Riding dirty\").\n\n==Music video==\nThe [[music video]] shows cops abusing their powers, though Chamillionaire does admit to various crimes of this being promoted, including [[DWI]] and [[prostitution]]. He juxtaposes police actions with [[professional wrestling|wrestling]] scenes to show how the police allegedly treat suspects. The music video, filmed in [[Dallas, Texas]], features [[cameo appearance]]s from [[Tom Lister Jr.]], [[Wish Bone]], [[Layzie Bone]], [[Play-N-Skillz]], [[Chingo Bling]], [[OG Ron C]], [[Big Tuck]], and Chamillionaire's younger brother Rasaq.\n\n==Reception==\nThe song topped the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] in the U.S. for two weeks and peaked at number two in the [[United Kingdom]], behind [[Shakira]] when it was released.  At the [[49th Annual Grammy Awards]], \"Ridin'\" won [[Grammy Award for Best Rap Performance by a Duo or Group|Best Rap Performance by a Duo or Group]] and received a nomination for [[Grammy Award for Best Rap Song|Best Rap Song]]. It was awarded the last [[Best Rap Video]] at the [[MTV Video Music Awards]] in 2006. The song ranked number three on ''[[Rolling Stone]]'s'' \"100 Best Songs of 2006\" and #6 on BET's \"Top 100 Music Videos Of 2006\". It was the best selling ringtone in 2006, with 3.2 million sales, certified by the RIAA as the first multi-platinum Mastertone artist in history.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.houstonpress.com/music/remember-when-ringtone-rap-ruled-the-world-7751438|title=Remember when ringtone rap ruled the world?|first=Brandon|last=Caldwell|work=Houston Press|date=2015-09-11|accessdate=2016-09-20}}</ref>\n\nThe song is played after [[Houston Astros]] victories and has also become an [[Internet meme]] in image macros. Spunk rock band [[Zolof the Rock and Roll Destroyer]] has covered the song live. ''[[Ridin' Dirty]]'' is the title of the 1996 album by [[UGK]]. Chamillionaire often cites this as one of his all-time favorite records.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://allhiphop.com/2005/09/14/chamillionaire-here-comes-the-reign/|title=Chamillionaire: Here comes the reign|first=Bill|last=Heinzelman|publisher=All Hip-Hop|date=2005-09-14|accessdate=2016-09-20}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n\"Ridin'\" debuted on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] at number 88 the week of February 25, 2006.<ref name=\"Budging\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/59610/no-budging-beyonce-from-hot-100-no-1|title=No Budging Beyonc\u00e9 From Hot 100 No. 1|last=Hope|first=Clover|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=February 23, 2006|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> Eight weeks later, it moved eight spots from number 12 to number 4 the week of April 29, 2006<ref name=\"Powter\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/58614/charts-powter-stays-hot-bon-jovi-scores-with-country|title=Charts: Powter Stays Hot, Bon Jovi Scores With Country|last=Hope|first=Clover|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=April 27, 2006|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> and stayed there for two weeks.<ref name=\"Rihanna\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/58468/rihanna-stays-strong-on-hot-100|title=Rihanna Stays Strong On Hot 100|last=Hope|first=Clover|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=May 11, 2006|accessdate=September 12, 2014}}</ref> It peaked at number one and stayed there for two weeks. This gave both artists their first Hot 100 number-one hit in their career. It stayed on the chart for thirty-one weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acharts.us/song/7860|title=Chamillionaire and Krayzie Bone - Ridin'|publisher=aCharts.us|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref>  In New Zealand, the song debuted at number 3, then moved to number 2 the next week where it peaked at and stayed for 7 consecutive weeks, being kept from the top by Nelly Furtado's Promiscuous, which topped the chart for 5 weeks, then Justin Timberlake's Sexyback, which dethroned Furtado and kept Ridin at number 2.\n\n==Later adaptation==\nOn July 17, 2006, Chamillionaire announced via bulletin on his official [[Myspace]] page that American [[parody|parodist]] [[\"Weird Al\" Yankovic]] recorded a parody of \"Ridin'\" for his new album ''[[Straight Outta Lynwood]]'' (released on September 26, 2006). The parody, called \"[[White & Nerdy]]\" also featured a music video and was released as the lead single from the album.\nChamillionaire stated in an interview that he enjoyed the parody of the song written by Yankovic, and was surprised by Yankovic's rapping ability.<ref>[http://www.mtv.com/bands/m/mixtape_monday/091106/ MTVNews.com story] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140314085731/http://www.mtv.com/bands/m/mixtape_monday/091106/ |date=March 14, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n'''UK 12\"'''<ref name=\"UK Vinyl\">{{cite web|url=http://www.discogs.com/Chamillionaire-Feat-Krayzie-Bone-Ridin/release/1800313|title=Chamillionaire Feat. Krayzie Bone - Ridin' (Vinyl)|publisher=[[Discogs]]|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref>\n# \"Ridin'\" (Album Version)\n# \"Ridin'\" (UK Remix) (featuring [[Sway DaSafo|Sway]])\n# \"Ridin'\" (Instrumental)\n\n'''UK CD'''<ref name=\"UK CD1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.discogs.com/Chamillionaire-Feat-Krayzie-Bone-Ridin/release/4877112|title=Chamillionaire Feat. Krayzie Bone - Ridin' (CD)|publisher=Discogs|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref>\n# \"Ridin'\" (Radio Edit) \u2013 3:45\n# \"Ridin'\" (Album Version) \u2013 5:03\n\n'''UK CD \u2013 Enhanced'''<ref name=\"UK CD2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.discogs.com/Chamillionaire-Feat-Krayzie-Bone-Ridin/release/3940902|title=Chamillionaire Feat. Krayzie Bone - Ridin' (CD)|publisher=Discogs|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref>\n# \"Ridin'\" (Album Version)\n# \"Think I'm Crazy\"\n# \"Ridin'\" (UK Remix) (featuring Sway)\n# \"Ridin'\" (Instrumental)\n# \"Ridin'\" (Video)\n\n'''US CD \u2013 maxi single (Promo)'''<ref name=\"US CD\">{{cite web|url=http://www.discogs.com/Chamillionaire-featuring-Krayzie-Bone-Ridin/release/4576904|title=Chamillionaire featuring Krayzie Bone - Ridin'|publisher=Discogs|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref>\n# \"Ridin'\" (Radio Edit) (featuring [[Krayzie Bone]]) \u2013 4:07\n# \"Ridin'\" (Main) (featuring Krayzie Bone) \u2013 5:06\n# \"Ridin'\" (Instrumental) \u2013 4:58\n\n==Remixes and parodies==\nThe remixes feature the following artists:\n* Houston Remix (official) \u2013 [[UGK]] & [[Pimp C]]\n* NYC Remix (official) \u2013 [[Papoose (rapper)|Papoose]] and [[Jae Millz]]\n* West Coast Remix (official) \u2013 [[The Game (rapper)|The Game]] and [[DJ Quik]]\n* \"Ridin' Overseas\" (official) \u2013 [[Akon]]\n* \"Ridin'\" Remix (unofficial) \u2013 [[Trae]] and [[Krayzie Bone]]\n* \"Ridin'\" UK Remix (official) \u2013 [[Sway DaSafo|Sway]]\n* \"Ridin'\" NZ Remix (official) \u2013 [[Tyree (rapper)|Tyree]]\n* \"Ridin'\" DJay.Jonny.Young Remix (official) \u2013 [[Papoose (rapper)|Papoose]]\n* \"[[White & Nerdy]]\" (official) Parody \u2013 [[\"Weird Al\" Yankovic]] (from ''[[Straight Outta Lynwood]]'')\n* \"Immigration'\" (official) Parody \u2013 [[Chingo Bling]] (from ''Chingo de Mayo'')\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Chart (2006)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|24|artist=Chamillionaire feat. Krayzie Bone|song=Ridin'|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|13|artist=Chamillionaire feat. Krayzie Bone|song=Ridin'|accessdate=September 13, 2014|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|40|artist=Chamillionaire feat. Krayzie Bone|song=